{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So I am a pediatric cancer doctor"},{"time":3000,"text":"and stem-cell researcher at Stanford University"},{"time":7000,"text":"where my clinical focus has been bone marrow transplantation."},{"time":10000,"text":"Now, inspired by Jill Bolte Taylor last year,"},{"time":12000,"text":"I didn't bring a human brain,"},{"time":14000,"text":"but I did bring a liter of bone marrow."},{"time":17000,"text":"And bone marrow is actually what we use"},{"time":20000,"text":"to save the lives of tens of thousands of patients,"},{"time":22000,"text":"most of whom have advanced malignancies like leukemia and lymphoma"},{"time":25000,"text":"and some other diseases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27000,"text":"So, a few years ago, I'm doing my transplant fellowship at Stanford."},{"time":31000,"text":"I'm in the operating room. We have Bob here,"},{"time":33000,"text":"who is a volunteer donor."},{"time":35000,"text":"We're sending his marrow across the country to save the life"},{"time":37000,"text":"of a child with leukemia."},{"time":39000,"text":"So actually how do we harvest this bone marrow?"},{"time":41000,"text":"Well we have a whole O.R. team, general anesthesia, nurses,"},{"time":45000,"text":"and another doctor across from me."},{"time":47000,"text":"Bob's on the table, and we take this sort of small needle,"},{"time":49000,"text":"you know, not too big."},{"time":51000,"text":"And the way we do this is we basically"},{"time":53000,"text":"place this through the soft tissue,"},{"time":55000,"text":"and kind of punch it into the hard bone,"},{"time":57000,"text":"into the tuchus -- that's a technical term --"},{"time":59000,"text":"and aspirate about 10 mls of bone marrow out,"},{"time":63000,"text":"each time, with a syringe."},{"time":65000,"text":"And hand it off to the nurse. She squirts it into a tin."},{"time":68000,"text":"Hands it back to me. And we do that again and again."},{"time":71000,"text":"About 200 times usually."},{"time":73000,"text":"And by the end of this my arm is sore, I've got a callus on my hand,"},{"time":75000,"text":"let alone Bob,"},{"time":77000,"text":"whose rear end looks something more like this,"},{"time":79000,"text":"like Swiss cheese."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81000,"text":"So I'm thinking, you know, this procedure hasn't changed in about 40 years."},{"time":85000,"text":"And there is probably a better way to do this."},{"time":87000,"text":"So I thought of a minimally invasive approach,"},{"time":90000,"text":"and a new device that we call the Marrow Miner."},{"time":92000,"text":"This is it."},{"time":94000,"text":"And the Marrow Miner, the way it works is shown here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97000,"text":"Our standard see-through patient."},{"time":99000,"text":"Instead of entering the bone dozens of times,"},{"time":101000,"text":"we enter just once, into the front of the hip or the back of the hip."},{"time":103000,"text":"And we have a flexible, powered catheter"},{"time":106000,"text":"with a special wire loop tip that stays inside the crunchy part of the marrow"},{"time":109000,"text":"and follows the contours of the hip, as it moves around."},{"time":112000,"text":"So it enables you to very rapidly aspirate,"},{"time":114000,"text":"or suck out, rich bone marrow very quickly through one hole."},{"time":117000,"text":"We can do multiple passes through that same entry."},{"time":119000,"text":"No robots required."},{"time":121000,"text":"And, so, very quickly, Bob can just get one puncture, local anesthesia,"},{"time":124000,"text":"and do this harvest as an outpatient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128000,"text":"So I did a few prototypes. I got a small little grant at Stanford."},{"time":131000,"text":"And played around with this a little bit."},{"time":133000,"text":"And our team members developed this technology."},{"time":135000,"text":"And eventually we got two large animals, and pig studies."},{"time":139000,"text":"And we found, to our surprise, that we not only got bone marrow out,"},{"time":141000,"text":"but we got 10 times the stem cell activity"},{"time":144000,"text":"in the marrow from the Marrow Miner, compared to the normal device."},{"time":146000,"text":"This device was just FDA approved in the last year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149000,"text":"Here is a live patient. You can see it following the flexible curves around."},{"time":152000,"text":"There will be two passes here, in the same patient, from the same hole."},{"time":155000,"text":"This was done under local anesthesia, as an outpatient."},{"time":157000,"text":"And we got, again, about three to six times more stem cells"},{"time":160000,"text":"than the standard approach done on the same patient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163000,"text":"So why should you care? Bone marrow is a very rich source of adult stem cells."},{"time":166000,"text":"You all know about embryonic stem cells."},{"time":168000,"text":"They've got great potential but haven't yet entered clinical trials."},{"time":171000,"text":"Adult stem cells are throughout our body,"},{"time":173000,"text":"including the blood-forming stem cells in our bone marrow,"},{"time":175000,"text":"which we've been using as a form of stem-cell therapy"},{"time":177000,"text":"for over 40 years."},{"time":179000,"text":"In the last decade there's been an explosion of use"},{"time":182000,"text":"of bone marrow stem cells to treat the patient's other diseases"},{"time":185000,"text":"such as heart disease, vascular disease,"},{"time":187000,"text":"orthopedics, tissue engineering,"},{"time":189000,"text":"even in neurology to treat Parkinson's"},{"time":191000,"text":"and diabetes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193000,"text":"We've just come out, we're commercializing, this year,"},{"time":195000,"text":"generation 2.0 of the Marrow Miner."},{"time":197000,"text":"The hope is that this gets more stem cells out,"},{"time":199000,"text":"which translates to better outcomes."},{"time":201000,"text":"It may encourage more people to sign up to be"},{"time":203000,"text":"potential live-saving bone marrow donors."},{"time":205000,"text":"It may even enable you to bank"},{"time":207000,"text":"your own marrow stem cells, when you're younger and healthier,"},{"time":209000,"text":"to use in the future should you need it."},{"time":212000,"text":"And ultimately -- and here's a picture of our"},{"time":214000,"text":"bone marrow transplant survivors,"},{"time":216000,"text":"who come together for a reunion each year at Stanford."},{"time":218000,"text":"Hopefully this technology will let us"},{"time":220000,"text":"have more of these survivors in the future."},{"time":222000,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}